1 Section 1. Section 13-3403, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 13-3403 (1) Except as otherwise provided in the Property Tax Growth
4 Limitation Act, for fiscal years beginning on or after July 1, 2025, a
5 political subdivision's property tax request for any year shall not
6 exceed its property tax request authority as determined under this
7 section. The preliminary property tax request authority for each
8 political subdivision shall be the amount of property taxes levied by the
9 county board of equalization pursuant to section 77-1601 for such
10 political subdivision in the prior fiscal year, less the sum of
11 exceptions utilized in the prior year pursuant to section 13-3404.
12 (2) In addition to the preliminary property tax request authority,
13 the political subdivision's property tax request authority may be
14 increased as follows by the product of:
15 (a) If public safety services as defined in section 13-320 account
16 for twenty percent or more of the amount of the political subdivision's
17 budget funded by property taxes, such political subdivision's property
18 tax request authority may be increased by:
19 (i) The product of (A) the amount of property taxes levied in the
20 prior year, less the sum of exceptions utilized in the prior year
21 pursuant to subdivisions (1) and (2) of section 13-3404 and (B) the
22 political subdivision's growth percentage; and
23 (ii) The product of (A) the amount of property taxes levied in the
24 prior year, less the sum of exceptions utilized in the prior year
25 pursuant to subdivisions (1) and (2) of section 13-3404 and (B) the
26 greater of zero or the inflation percentage; or
27 (b) If public safety services as defined in section 13-320 account
28 for less than twenty percent of the amount of the political subdivision's
29 budget funded by property taxes, such political subdivision's property
30 tax request authority may be increased by:
31 (i) The product of (A) the amount of property taxes levied in the
